place.name: WARNDON
place.gazetteerText: WARNDON, a parish in Droitwich district, Worcestershire; 2½ miles NE of Worcester r. station. Post town, Worcester. Acres, 988. Real property, £1,589. Pop., 164. Houses, 39. The property is all in one estate. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Worcester. Value, £151. Patron, R. Berkeley, Esq. The church is plain. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
